## Animation Guidelines

### Timing
- **Fast interactions**: 150-200ms (hover, focus)
- **Standard transitions**: 300-400ms (cards, modals)
- **Complex animations**: 600-800ms (page transitions)

### Easing Functions
- **Standard**: `ease-out` or `cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)`
- **Entrance**: `ease-out`
- **Exit**: `ease-in`
- **Complex**: `cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)`

### Transform Performance
- **ALWAYS** use `transform` and `opacity` for animations (GPU accelerated)
- **AVOID** animating `width`, `height`, `top`, `left` (causes reflow)
- Use `will-change` sparingly for complex animations

## Responsive Breakpoints

```css
/* Mobile First */
@media (min-width: 640px) { /* sm: Tablet */ }
@media (min-width: 1024px) { /* lg: Desktop - Enable Split Screen */ }
@media (min-width: 1280px) { /* xl: Large Desktop */ }
```

### Responsive Strategy
1. **Default (< 640px)**: Single column, stacked layout
2. **Tablet (640-1023px)**: Still stacked, larger typography
3. **Desktop (1024px+)**: Split-screen layout activates
4. **Large Desktop (1280px+)**: More spacious padding/margins

## Accessibility Requirements

### Keyboard Navigation
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Visible focus indicators using `--accent` color
- Logical tab order

### Color Contrast
- Text on background: minimum 4.5:1 ratio
- Large text (18px+): minimum 3:1 ratio
- UI components: minimum 3:1 ratio
- Test with both light and dark modes

### ARIA & Semantic HTML
- Use semantic HTML5 elements (`<header>`, `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`)
- Add ARIA labels where needed
- Alt text for all images
- Screen reader tested

### Reduced Motion
```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  * {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

## Performance Best Practices

### CSS
- Use CSS custom properties for theming
- Leverage GPU acceleration (`transform`, `opacity`)
- Minimize reflows and repaints
- Use `contain` property for isolated components

### Images
- Optimize PNGs and JPEGs
- Use WebP with fallbacks
- Lazy load below-the-fold images
- Provide proper width/height to prevent CLS

### JavaScript
- Minimal client-side JS (Astro islands)
- Use `client:load` only when necessary
- Debounce scroll handlers
- Use `requestAnimationFrame` for animations

## Code Style

### Tailwind Usage
- **DO**: Use utility classes directly in markup
- **DON'T**: Use `@apply` in CSS files
- **DO**: Use arbitrary values when needed: `bg-[var(--accent)]`
- **DON'T**: Create utility classes for one-off styles

### Component Organization
```astro
---
// 1. Imports
import Component from './Component.astro';

// 2. Props/Types
interface Props {
  title: string;
}

// 3. Component logic
const { title } = Astro.props;
---

<!-- 4. Template -->
<div>
  {/* content */}
</div>

<!-- 5. Scoped styles (minimal, prefer Tailwind) -->
<style>
  /* Only for unique styles not possible with Tailwind */
</style>
```

## Testing Requirements

### Visual Testing
- Test in both light and dark modes
- Test at all breakpoints (320px, 768px, 1024px, 1920px)
- Test with browser zoom at 200%
- Test with high contrast mode

### Functionality Testing
- Keyboard navigation
- Screen reader compatibility
- Form validation
- Animation performance (60fps)
- Cross-browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)

## When in Doubt

1. **Consistency**: Follow existing patterns in the codebase
2. **Simplicity**: Prefer simple solutions over clever ones
3. **Performance**: Measure don't guess
4. **Accessibility**: Include everyone
5. **Brand**: Stay true to the phoenix theme
